How to Connect to a Tinker Board from a Windows Computer Using VNC:

Download and install VNC Viewer on a Windows computer.
https://www.realvnc.com/en/connect/download/viewer/

Get the Tinker Board’s current IP address:
Open a terminal: Desktop > Home Icon > System > LXTerminal

sudo ip address

On the Windows computer launch VNC Viewer App:
  Go to: File > New Connection
  Enter the Tinker Board’s current IP address (ex. 192.168.1.81)
  Followed by a colon and the default port number 5901
  Example format: 192.168.1.1:5901
  Double click on the connection icon
  You should see a window open up with your Tinker Board’s desktop visible.
